AGENT AxiomDatasetBuilder
VERSION 1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 2
PURPOSE Build training datasets from the AXIOM repo for TinyLlama fine-tuning
GOAL Extract constitutional knowledge from every source in the repo
     Convert specifications, guards, bugs, and interactions into training examples
     Produce deduplicated JSONL ready for Colab fine-tuning

RECEIVES repo_path: string
EMITS training_data: jsonl, stats: dict, example_count: int
MUTATES examples_list, dedup_set
CANNOT_MUTATE agent, goal, version, trust_level, source_types, output_format, dedup_method

CONSTRAINT Every example must have instruction and output fields
CONSTRAINT Output must be longer than twenty characters to be included
CONSTRAINT Duplicate examples are removed by instruction hash before writing
CONSTRAINT Bad-rated examples from dev training files are excluded
CONSTRAINT Guard examples must include BUG-001 check reminder
CONSTRAINT All output is UTF-8 encoded JSONL
CONSTRAINT Training data never includes raw secrets or API keys

RULES
- Collect hard-coded bug pattern examples first — these are highest value
- Collect language knowledge examples — how AXIOM constructs work
- Collect guard writing examples — the canonical guard pattern
- Scan every axiom file in the repo and generate two examples per file
- For each axiom file: one explanation example and one spec-writing example
- Scan guard modules and extract pattern descriptions
- Scan guard modules and extract test case knowledge
- Load existing dev training files and filter by quality rating
- Load agent memory interactions and convert to training format
- Deduplicate all examples by instruction content hash before writing
- Write output as one JSON object per line in JSONL format

PROCESS
- Receive repo path from command line or default to current directory
- Phase 1: Add hard-coded bug patterns, language examples, guard examples
- Phase 2: Walk axiom_files directory recursively for all axiom specifications
- For each axiom file extract agent name, purpose, goal, constraints
- Generate explanation example from extracted fields
- Generate spec-writing example from full file content
- Phase 3: Walk guard directories for pattern modules
- Extract regex patterns with severity from guard tuple format
- Extract test cases from guard files or matching test directory
- Phase 4: Load axiom_dev_training.jsonl when available, skip bad-rated entries
- Phase 5: Load axiom_agent_memory.jsonl when available, filter for interactions
- Phase 6: Deduplicate by MD5 hash of instruction field
- Write deduplicated examples to axiom_training_data.jsonl
- Report total count, dedup count, file size, and next steps

CHECK
- Every example has non-empty instruction field
- Every example has output longer than twenty characters
- No duplicate instructions in final output
- Output file is valid JSONL with one object per line
- Bad-rated dev training entries are excluded
- Guard pattern extraction matches the actual guard tuple format
- Axiom file count matches expected range for the repo

FAILURE
- On empty repo path: use current directory as default
- On missing axiom_files directory: search from repo root directly
- On guard module read error: skip and continue to next module
- On training file parse error: skip malformed line and continue
- On zero examples generated: report error and suggest running dev agent first

OUTPUT
- axiom_training_data.jsonl: one JSON object per line
- Each object: instruction, input, output, source, type fields
- Stats display: total examples, by type breakdown, file size
- Next steps: upload path, Colab instructions, deployment commands

SUCCESS
coverage: 0.35
quality: 0.30
diversity: 0.20
dedup_rate: 0.15
